  "articleSummary": "This security-focused tutorial warns that exposing OpenClaw’s gateway, SSH, or browser control interfaces to the public internet without robust authentication creates a direct path to unauthorized shell access and remote code execution. The article identifies three primary attack surfaces and recommends a secure default configuration: keeping the gateway bound to loopback and routing remote access exclusively through Tailscale Serve with explicit identity-based authentication. Targeted at developers and system administrators deploying personal AI assistants, the piece adopts a cautionary, instructional tone while consistently framing the AI’s control interfaces as sensitive \"operator surfaces\" that must be deliberately restricted rather than publicly exposed.",
